title: A Life Too Short_ The Tragedy of Robert Enke
description:
A Life too Short:The Tragdey of Robert Enke



A Life too Short:The Tragdey of Robert Enke is a 2012 biography by Ronald Reng about Hannover 96 captain and Germany goalie Robert Enke, who committed suicide on 10 November 2009.

The book details the life of Robert Enke, particularly focusing on Enke's struggle with depression. Reng also focuses on his friendship with Enke, with whom he was supposed to co-write a biography.
